description:
Hellhole Canyon.

Measurements:
- plant with a single main stem, branched only in upper half.
- calyx in fl 2.0 mm; in fr to 3.8 mm.
- corolla width 2.0 mm
- nutlets 4, homomorphic, honkingly tubercled, 2.0 mm, triangular-ovate, 0.2 mm shorter than style.
When I first opened the calyx, the green nutlets had a rounded edge.  But after an hour, they developed the sharp edge seen in the photos.
Only one nutlet has a fairly clear median ridge.
